  "prompt": "How do you simplify \u221a(75yz^2)?",
  "response": "Let's solve this step by step:\n\n1) First, break down 75 into its prime factors:\n   \u2022 75 = 3 \u00d7 5\u00b2 \n\n2) To simplify \u221a(75yz^2), we want to take out the largest perfect square factor possible\n\n3) From 75, the largest perfect square factor is 25 (5\u00b2)\n   \u2022 75 = 25 \u00d7 3\n\n4) Rewrite the square root:\n   \u221a(75yz^2) = \u221a(25 \u00d7 3 \u00d7 yz^2)\n             = \u221a(25) \u00d7 \u221a(3) \u00d7 \u221a(yz^2)\n\n5) Simplify \u221a(25):\n   \u2022 \u221a(25) = 5\n\n6) Simplify \u221a(yz^2):\n   \u2022 First, take out the largest perfect square from y and z^2\n   \u2022 \u221a(yz^2) = \u221ay \u00d7 \u221a(z^2) = \u221ay \u00d7 z\n\n7) Put it all together:\n   \u221a(75yz^2) = 5 \u00d7 \u221a3 \u00d7 \u221ay \u00d7 z\n             = 5z\u221a(3y)\n\nTherefore, \u221a(75yz^2) = 5z\u221a(3y)",
